Date: 1999-11-26

Title: Matrix difference equations for the supersymmetric Lie algebra sl(2,1)

and the `off-shell' Bethe ansatzAuthors: T. Quella

Comments: 10 pages, LaTex, references and acknowledgements added, spl(2,1) now

called sl(2,1)Journal-ref: J.Phys. A33 (2000) 2579-2586

Based on the rational R-matrix of the supersymmetric sl(2,1) matrixdifference equations are solved by means of a generalization of the nestedalgebraic Bethe ansatz. These solutions are shown to be of highest-weight withrespect to the underlying graded Lie algebra structure.